6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to railroads; defining terms;
providing for type of identification required to be
8 shown following a railroad accident or incident;
providing for codification; and declaring an
9 emergency.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 104 of Title 66, unless there is
15 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. As used in this section:
17 1. "FRA-certified conductor" means a conductor, switchman,
18 brakeman, trainman, or fireman licensed and certified by the Federal
19 Railroad Administration (FRA);
20 2. "FRA-certified engineer" means an engineer licensed and
21 certified by the FRA;
22 3. "Railroad accident or incident" means accidents involving to
23 persons, including pedestrians, motor vehicles, and animals,
24
