1 inci dental to and as a consequence of the flow of vehicles and
2 pedestrians along the railroads of Oklahoma; and
3 4. "Railroad management" means any rail employee overseeing and
4 assisting in the operation of rail transit.
5 B. For identification purposes, no railroad employee involved
6 in a railroad accident or incident shall be required to show his or
7 her driver license to law enforcement or other safety officer.
8 Railroad employees shall be allowed to show the following
9 identification:
10 1. A FRA-certified conductor shall provide his or her FRA
11 certification;
12 2. A FRA-certified engineer shall provide his or her FRA
13 certification; and
14 3. Railroad management shall provide his or her FRA
15 certification.
16 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
17 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
18 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
19 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
